According to your explanation i think you want to know about KeyboardAvoidingView in react native. This is a component to solve the common problem of views that need to move out of the way of the virtual keyboard. It can automatically adjust either its height, position, or bottom padding based on the position of the keyboard.

    import {KeyboardAvoidingView} from &#39;react-native&#39;;

    &lt;ScrollView&gt;
         &lt;KeyboardAvoidingView style={styles.container} behavior=&quot;padding&quot; enabled&gt;
            ... your UI ...
            //place your all inputs here
         &lt;/KeyboardAvoidingView&gt;;
    &lt;/ScrollView&gt;

The behavior prop can be changed to 

      1. height
      2. position
      3. padding

You can change it accordingly to your design.

Checkout the documentation to know more - https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/0.60/keyboardavoidingview

